# Ethereum Community Hub Mauritius – 12 Month Roadmap

This roadmap outlines the key milestones and objectives for the first year of the Ethereum Community Hub Mauritius.

The goal is to progressively grow the local Ethereum ecosystem through education, developer onboarding, and community building.

---

# Phase 1 – Hub Launch (Months 1–3)

Focus: Community foundation and awareness.

Activities:

• Official launch of the Ethereum Community Hub Mauritius
• First community meetups introducing Ethereum and Web3
• Outreach to universities and student communities
• Creation of online community channels (Telegram, LinkedIn, Twitter, Facebook)
• Introductory workshops on blockchain fundamentals and Ethereum basics

Expected outcomes:

• First 50–100 community members
• Partnerships initiated with universities
• First developer onboarding sessions

---

# Phase 2 – Developer Engagement (Months 4–6)

Focus: Technical education and builder engagement.

Activities:

• Smart contract development workshops
• Solidity introduction bootcamp
• Community co-working days for builders
• First local hackathon focused on Ethereum use cases

Expected outcomes:

• 10–20 developers actively building
• First experimental projects created
• Stronger collaboration between students and builders

---

# Phase 3 – Ecosystem Expansion (Months 7–9)

Focus: real-world use cases and partnerships.

Activities:

• Launch of NFT program for local artists
• NFT education workshops for creators
• Web3 entrepreneurship sessions
• Collaboration with startups and tech communities

Expected outcomes:

• First NFT collections from Mauritian artists
• Increased participation from creators and entrepreneurs
• Growing recognition of the hub within the local tech ecosystem

---

# Phase 4 – Regional Impact (Months 10–12)

Focus: ecosystem maturity and regional connections.

Activities:

• Second Ethereum hackathon
• Demo day showcasing community projects
• Collaboration with African Web3 communities
• Expansion of educational programs

Expected outcomes:

• 200+ community members
• Multiple Ethereum-based projects created
• Mauritius positioned as an emerging Ethereum community hub in the region

---

# Long-Term Vision

The Ethereum Community Hub Mauritius aims to become:

• A center for Ethereum education in Mauritius
• A gateway connecting African builders to the global Ethereum ecosystem
• A space where developers, creators, and entrepreneurs collaborate on real-world blockchain applications
